@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}


<div class="row">
    <h4>Headings -> titles displayed on the page, 6 levels - h1,h1,...,h6 -> the higher the level, the less prominent the heading</h4>

    <p>p element makes all text inside it a distinct paragraph.</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Wrapping inside "ul" tag tells browser that whatever is inside should be rendered as an unordered list</li>
        <li>To denote particular element, wrap them in "li" tags</li>
        <li>Strict rule -> "ul" element shoul only contain "li" elements</li>
    </ul>

    <ol>
        <li>"ol" tag for ordered list</li>
        <li>Each element is also "li", but numbers increment on their own</li>

    </ol>
    <p>Above -> block eleemnts, below -> inline elements</p>
    <p><em>Here is</em> italic inline element</p>
    <p><strong>Here is</strong> inline tag for bold text</p>
    <p><em><strong>Italic and bold!!</strong></em></p>
    @*<p><em>Check the order of tags</p></em>*@

    <p>Here is the <br/>line break, using "br" tag, that is emty(self-closing)</p>
    <p>Here is the horisontal rule, that represents a thematic break (also empty):</p>
    <hr/>

    <p>Ypu can also use empty tags <br>without slash</p> 
    <hr>

    <p></p>

</div>
